history.content:
I'm a sophomore who was hoping EECS16A could've been satisfied by PHY89 (I've taken it as a physics major). I was going to take the 47D bridge course for 16A next semester, but if the same freshman/sophomore restrictions apply to 16B, could I take EECS47D and 16B simultaneously next semester? I've already done an experimentation course with circuits.

I'd really wish to avoid having summer as an option, but would it work then?
history.subject: Concurrent enrollment into 16A bridge course and 16B?
